### 1. Register User
POST http://localhost:3002/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "testuser@example.com",
    "password": "securePass123",
    "name": "Test User"
}

### 2. Login User (Copy the accessToken from response)
# @name login
POST http://localhost:3002/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "testuser@example.com",
    "password": "securePass123"
}

### 3. Access Protected Route (Me)
# Replace {{login.response.body.accessToken}} with your actual token if automatic variable doesn't work
GET http://localhost:3002/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### 4. Admin Route (Should Fail for Normal User)
GET http://localhost:3002/auth/admin
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### 5. Refresh Token (Uses Cookie Automatically)
POST http://localhost:3002/auth/refresh

### 6. Logout
POST http://localhost:3002/auth/logout
